The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 06 June is 42,430 (4,911 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 01 June, there were 153 new confirmed cases (17.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 25 May, there were 59 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 159% (94 extra cases).
